[
  {
    "text": "♪ Mellow instrumental hip-hop ♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=4"
  },
  {
    "text": "Hello! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=10"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm Kellie, and I'm a Platform Compatibility Engineer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPadOS and iOS are powerful platforms. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "You already have a great app built for them, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "maybe you even have multiple. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now you can easily run those same apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=24"
  },
  {
    "text": "on Apple's latest platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=26"
  },
  {
    "text": "The majority of iOS apps look and feel great ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=29"
  },
  {
    "text": "right out of the box. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, check out the iPad Calendar app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "running unmodified in the simulator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "It looks and feels just like iPad ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "and everything works exactly as I would expect. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=44"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can see different timelines, zoom into details ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=47"
  },
  {
    "text": "about specific events, and add new ones.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=50"
  },
  {
    "text": "And Maps, which runs in its iPad version ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=60"
  },
  {
    "text": "following the recommendations I'm about to cover. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=63"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can spin the globe beautifully. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=66"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can also look up specific destinations...",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "...and visit famous landmarks.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this video, I'll introduce iPad and iPhone apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "on this new platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=90"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll start by covering the built-in behaviors ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "your app gets for free.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, I'll talk about the functional differences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=98"
  },
  {
    "text": "your app should be aware of and what you should do about them. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, I'll explain how to decide ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "whether the Designed for iPad experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=107"
  },
  {
    "text": "is best suited to your app's needs.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=110"
  },
  {
    "text": "This new platform is built on the foundations of iOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "We enhance that shared bedrock with additional system support. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "The combination of the two makes it more than likely ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=124"
  },
  {
    "text": "that your app will run beautifully ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "without changing anything! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPad and iPhone apps are displayed as windows ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=133"
  },
  {
    "text": "on this device, in their light mode style. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=135"
  },
  {
    "text": "The system prefers the iPad variant of your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "in landscape orientation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "but if your app only supports iPhone, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=145"
  },
  {
    "text": "the system displays it with an iPhone aspect ratio ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=147"
  },
  {
    "text": "in portrait orientation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app supports multiple orientations, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "a rotation button is provided above the top-right corner ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "of your window, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=159"
  },
  {
    "text": "so people can rotate each scene to their preference. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "When you grab the corners of your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=165"
  },
  {
    "text": "the system scales its window, preserving the aspect ratio. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "When you reach the minimum or maximum size, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "the corners bounce to reflect that. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=175"
  },
  {
    "text": "The scaling is managed by the system ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "so your app gets all of this support for free. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "People interact with content on this device via natural input. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=185"
  },
  {
    "text": "They look at something and tap their fingers together ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=190"
  },
  {
    "text": "to select it or reach out and touch content directly. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=192"
  },
  {
    "text": "They may also use a Bluetooth trackpad or game controller. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "All of these system-defined interaction methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=201"
  },
  {
    "text": "send events that your app is already familiar with ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=204"
  },
  {
    "text": "so you can continue to leverage ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=207"
  },
  {
    "text": "the same event-handling techniques that you already use. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "System views like the document manager and photo picker ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "match the system appearance to help your app fit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=217"
  },
  {
    "text": "into the look and feel of the platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=220"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app supports Touch ID or Face ID, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=225"
  },
  {
    "text": "LocalAuthentication automatically forwards ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=228"
  },
  {
    "text": "those implementations through Optic ID ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=230"
  },
  {
    "text": "so your app supports the latest authentication technology ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "without any additional work on your part. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=237"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, there are a few things that are different ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "about this platform compared to iOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=244"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apps on this device can be viewed in portrait or landscape. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=248"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's nothing new compared to iPad. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=252"
  },
  {
    "text": "But unlike iPad, there's no notion of rotating ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "the entire device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "Because the device's orientation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=261"
  },
  {
    "text": "doesn't inform your app's orientation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may want to specify which orientation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "your app prefers for new scenes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=268"
  },
  {
    "text": "People can still rotate scenes later ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "via the system rotation button. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can express a preference by adding the new ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "UIPreferredDefaultInterface Orientation key ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=279"
  },
  {
    "text": "to your app's Info.plist. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=282"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you don't provide one, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=285"
  },
  {
    "text": "the system will use its default orientation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "This key is unique to this platform ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "and will not affect other platforms. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=292"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are a couple other plist keys ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=295"
  },
  {
    "text": "that also have special meaning on this device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=297"
  },
  {
    "text": "even though they're not new. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=299"
  },
  {
    "text": "The system uses UISupportedInterfaceOrientations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=302"
  },
  {
    "text": "to decide if your app's windows need a rotation button, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "and App Store Connect relies on UIRequiredDeviceCapabilities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "to determine if your app is compatible with this new device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=314"
  },
  {
    "text": "All suitable apps are automatically made available ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the App Store. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=321"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app relies on specific features ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=323"
  },
  {
    "text": "which are not available on this device ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "or if there's a reason your app doesn't make sense ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "on this platform, you can manage availability ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "in App Store Connect. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=332"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "watch \"Explore App Store Connect for spatial computing.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "Take a moment to add those keys to your Info.plist if necessary ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "or confirm the existing values are still accurate ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "and up to date. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=347"
  },
  {
    "text": "Gestures on this device work differently ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=349"
  },
  {
    "text": "since folks use their eyes and hands to interact with content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=351"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are a maximum of two simultaneous inputs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=356"
  },
  {
    "text": "as each hand is a distinct touch. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=360"
  },
  {
    "text": "All system gestures that expect two touches or fewer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=363"
  },
  {
    "text": "work seamlessly. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=367"
  },
  {
    "text": "Custom gesture recognizers are also supported, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=369"
  },
  {
    "text": "but you may need to update them to run smoothly ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=373"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the natural input expectations. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=375"
  },
  {
    "text": "One of the most updated frameworks is ARKit ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=380"
  },
  {
    "text": "which has evolved significantly to be more powerful than ever. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=383"
  },
  {
    "text": "We've designed new APIs and experiences from the ground up ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=387"
  },
  {
    "text": "to account for fundamental differences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=391"
  },
  {
    "text": "in platform architecture and privacy needs. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=394"
  },
  {
    "text": "That means your existing ARViews and ARSessions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=397"
  },
  {
    "text": "won't work on this device as they do on iPad and iPhone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=401"
  },
  {
    "text": "Check out ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=406"
  },
  {
    "text": "the \"Re-imagine your ARKit app for spatial experiences\" video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "to learn about all the new ARKit capabilities you can leverage ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=411"
  },
  {
    "text": "by rebuilding your app for this platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=414"
  },
  {
    "text": "Location support for this device is a lot like iPad: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=418"
  },
  {
    "text": "location can be approximated via Wi-Fi or shared via iPhone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=422"
  },
  {
    "text": "More details are provided ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=427"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the \"Meet Core Location for spatial computing\" video. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "Look to Dictate is a convenient new input technique ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=433"
  },
  {
    "text": "that allows people to quickly navigate through an app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=436"
  },
  {
    "text": "using only their eyes and voice. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=438"
  },
  {
    "text": "When enabled, a microphone icon ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "replaces the magnifying glass in search fields, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=443"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you can look at the microphone and speak to search.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "This API is offered on search bars. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=457"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's disabled by default for iPad and iPhone apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=460"
  },
  {
    "text": "running on this platform to allow you to verify the behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "and decide where you want to enable it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=467"
  },
  {
    "text": "And it's a no-op on iOS and iPadOS, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=470"
  },
  {
    "text": "so there's no need to conditionalize your support ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=473"
  },
  {
    "text": "by platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=475"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can enable Look to Dictate in SwiftUI by adding ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "the .searchDictationBehavior() modifier ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": "to your searchable view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=483"
  },
  {
    "text": "For UIKit search bars, set isLookToDictateEnabled to true. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=485"
  },
  {
    "text": "The best way to handle all of these changes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=492"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the same way you always have: use availability checks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=495"
  },
  {
    "text": "Make sure that a framework is supported ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=500"
  },
  {
    "text": "before calling into it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=502"
  },
  {
    "text": "Many frameworks even have those functions built in ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=505"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your convenience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=507"
  },
  {
    "text": "Don't forget to do the same thing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "when accessing configurations that rely on the presence ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=512"
  },
  {
    "text": "of specific hardware. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=514"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, the headset has many more cameras ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=517"
  },
  {
    "text": "than just the front and back cameras on iOS devices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=519"
  },
  {
    "text": "but not all of those are available for apps to use. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=523"
  },
  {
    "text": "Verify that a camera is present and supported before you use it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=526"
  },
  {
    "text": "These practices make your app more robust on every device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=532"
  },
  {
    "text": "not just this one. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=536"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's only a sampling of the framework evolution ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=538"
  },
  {
    "text": "on this platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=540"
  },
  {
    "text": "Some frameworks have grown a lot ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=542"
  },
  {
    "text": "and have videos specifically dedicated to this device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=544"
  },
  {
    "text": "like SwiftUI, ARKit, and RealityKit. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=547"
  },
  {
    "text": "Most of the remaining frameworks work as they always have ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=551"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a few tweaks to how you adopt them. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=555"
  },
  {
    "text": "Detailed information about all of the modified frameworks ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=557"
  },
  {
    "text": "is available in the developer documentation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=560"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now that you have a sense of what code changes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=564"
  },
  {
    "text": "are necessary for your app, you're ready for action. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=566"
  },
  {
    "text": "When the xrOS SDK is installed, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=570"
  },
  {
    "text": "Xcode automatically adds xrOS Device (Designed for iPad) ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=572"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Supported Destinations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=576"
  },
  {
    "text": "for projects that use the iOS SDK. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=578"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your scheme sets a different platform or auto for the SDK, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=582"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can add the Designed for iPad target manually. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=586"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once that's set up, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=590"
  },
  {
    "text": "a run destination with the matching name ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=591"
  },
  {
    "text": "will appear in the destination picker. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=594"
  },
  {
    "text": "Select that target, build, and run. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=597"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's all there is to it! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=600"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPad and iPhone apps provide a fantastic experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=603"
  },
  {
    "text": "on this device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=606"
  },
  {
    "text": "Most apps don't need any changes at all, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=608"
  },
  {
    "text": "thanks to extensive system support. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=611"
  },
  {
    "text": "Whether you want to stick with building your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=614"
  },
  {
    "text": "against the iOS SDK or rebuild against the xrOS SDK ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=616"
  },
  {
    "text": "depends on your goals. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=621"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like I discussed earlier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=624"
  },
  {
    "text": "there are differences in which frameworks ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=625"
  },
  {
    "text": "are available for each SDK, as well as differences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=627"
  },
  {
    "text": "in supported features within each framework. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=630"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are two big things I want to call out ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=634"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are only available in the iOS SDK: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=636"
  },
  {
    "text": "SpriteKit and storyboards. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=639"
  },
  {
    "text": "If either of these technologies is integral to your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=642"
  },
  {
    "text": "you need to stick with designing for iPad. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=646"
  },
  {
    "text": "iPad and iPhone apps are displayed in windows ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=650"
  },
  {
    "text": "that feel just like iPad in their light mode style. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=652"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's what Maps looks like ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=656"
  },
  {
    "text": "when zoomed into the Sydney Opera House. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=658"
  },
  {
    "text": "Notice how the content fills all the way ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=661"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the edges of the window but doesn't extend past it, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=663"
  },
  {
    "text": "and all of the colors match the same light mode style ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=667"
  },
  {
    "text": "that Maps uses on iPad and iPhone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=670"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apps designed for xrOS unlock another level ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=674"
  },
  {
    "text": "of immersive, spatial experiences. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=677"
  },
  {
    "text": "Several frameworks, like ARKit and RealityKit, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=681"
  },
  {
    "text": "have evolved functionality that's only available ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=684"
  },
  {
    "text": "in apps designed for this platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=687"
  },
  {
    "text": "Refer to the other videos or the documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=690"
  },
  {
    "text": "to learn about all the new experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=693"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are possible thanks to these updates. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=695"
  },
  {
    "text": "In addition to windows, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "apps designed for this device also support volumes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=701"
  },
  {
    "text": "to display 3D objects in containers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=704"
  },
  {
    "text": "that grow to fit their contents, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=707"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as Immersive Spaces for immersive experiences. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=709"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's what the Keynote rehearsal space looks like ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=714"
  },
  {
    "text": "in headset. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=716"
  },
  {
    "text": "By hiding passthrough and other apps, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=718"
  },
  {
    "text": "Keynote keeps you fully immersed and focused ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=720"
  },
  {
    "text": "on your presentation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=723"
  },
  {
    "text": "In both the headset and the simulator, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=725"
  },
  {
    "text": "apps designed for this platform use the system look and feel. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=728"
  },
  {
    "text": "Their backgrounds are a glass material ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=732"
  },
  {
    "text": "that grounds people in their surroundings ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=734"
  },
  {
    "text": "and dynamically adjusts color balance and contrast ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=737"
  },
  {
    "text": "to promote legibility. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=740"
  },
  {
    "text": "They can also take advantage of the new Ornament API. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=743"
  },
  {
    "text": "Like the tab bar on the left and buttons at the bottom of Photos, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=747"
  },
  {
    "text": "ornaments anchor to the sides of a window ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=752"
  },
  {
    "text": "to enhance its functionality. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=754"
  },
  {
    "text": "And they leave the app more room to draw within the window. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=756"
  },
  {
    "text": "Most frequently, ornaments are used for navigation or toolbars. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=760"
  },
  {
    "text": "Designing for xrOS is perfect for apps that want to create ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=767"
  },
  {
    "text": "immersive experiences, adopt new framework functionality, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=770"
  },
  {
    "text": "or match the system look and feel. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=774"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you would rather preserve your app's existing experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=777"
  },
  {
    "text": "designing for iPad is the road for you. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=780"
  },
  {
    "text": "This platform shares a common foundation with iOS and iPadOS, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=784"
  },
  {
    "text": "so no matter which SDK you choose, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=788"
  },
  {
    "text": "the work you do for those platforms ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=790"
  },
  {
    "text": "will continue to benefit your experience on this one. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=793"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you decide that designing for this new platform ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=797"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the best fit for your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=799"
  },
  {
    "text": "the \"Meet SwiftUI for spatial computing\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=801"
  },
  {
    "text": "and \"Meet UIKit for spatial computing\" videos ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=804"
  },
  {
    "text": "are great places to start. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=806"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your next step is to try your app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=810"
  },
  {
    "text": "on this exciting new platform! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=811"
  },
  {
    "text": "The vast majority of apps work without any code changes at all. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=814"
  },
  {
    "text": "Pay special attention to the compatibility areas I covered: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=818"
  },
  {
    "text": "ensure your Info.plist keys are up to date, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=823"
  },
  {
    "text": "opt into new platform experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=825"
  },
  {
    "text": "you're interested in, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=827"
  },
  {
    "text": "and verify that your framework dependencies ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=829"
  },
  {
    "text": "are available before you use them. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=831"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you've done all that, watch ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=835"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Enhance your iPad and iPhone apps for the Shared Space\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=836"
  },
  {
    "text": "to learn how to make your iOS app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=840"
  },
  {
    "text": "feel right at home on this device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=842"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thanks for watching, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=845"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I look forward to trying your app on this new platform. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=846"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023-10090/?time=849"
  }
]